<item>
            <title>[PIG-2453] Fetching schema can be very slow for multi-thousand LOADs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2453</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a user tries to load resources with thousands of files using PigStorage, we spend an inordinate amount of time looking for schema files. This is because we check for a schema file per loaded file.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12536769">PIG-2453</key>
            <summary>Fetching schema can be very slow for multi-thousand LOADs</summary>
